9.6 monitoring system activity with top

top is an important command to use

top is a dashboard to monitor system activity. There are alternatives but top is installed by default

press f to show and selct from displayed fields

press M to filter by memory usage

press W to display new settings

us - processes in user space
sys - processes in system space
ni - processes that have had their priority changed with nice
id - idle, percent idle
wa- percent of time waiting for io. high values are bad
hi - hardware interrupt, this is the time the cpu is waiting for hardware
si - software interrupt


press F to adjust the fields you want displayed

press k to kill a process. You can choose the PID of the process you want to kill